<paragraph blockId="5.[445,756,276,299]" box="[445,756,276,299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[445,756,276,299]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[445,756,276,299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[525,756,276,299]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,614,276,299]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
Leach, 1817
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[495,707,306,325]" box="[495,707,306,325]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">(Figs 1–7, 17A–B, 18A)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,230,350,373]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Larvae of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[459,544,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,544,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily distinguishable from almost all other
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[113,269,414,437]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydrophilidae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of tracheal gills on the abdominal segments (Fig. 1) and the reduction of spiracular atrium (
<figureCitation box="[485,571,478,501]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[113,144,1333,1352]" captionTargetBox="[163,1044,222,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[150,1053,214,1318]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Third instar larva of Berosus (Berosus) japonicus Sharp, 1873, dorsal; A – head capsule; B – anterior margin of head capsule; C – detail of setae of gFR2; D – spiracular atrium; E – spiracle in spiracular atrium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" box="[113,584,510,533]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[113,201,510,533]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,201,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae often resemble 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[470,584,510,533]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[470,584,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Laccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" box="[113,584,542,565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Erichson, 
<quantity box="[227,313,542,565]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66598" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" unit="in" value="1837.0">1837 in</quantity>
head morphology (e.g.,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="ARCHANGELSKY M." box="[113,343,574,597]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 207" refId="ref14684" refString="ARCHANGELSKY M. 1997: Studies on the biology, ecology, and systematics of the immature stages of New World Hydrophiloidea (Coleoptera: Staphyliniformia). Bulletin of the Ohio Biological Survey, New Series 12: 1 - 207." type="book chapter" year="1997">ARCHANGELSKY 1997</bibRefCitation>
), however 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[469,555,574,597]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[469,555,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable by the morphology of the clypeolabrum: right epistomal lobe absent in
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[113,198,670,693]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,198,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[212,301,670,693]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[113,144,912,931]" captionTargetBox="[131,1083,223,861]" captionTargetId="figure-267@9.[113,1088,220,876]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 3. First instar larva of Berosus (Berosus) japonicus Sharp, 1873, anterior margin of head capsule, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) (both drawn from dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303137" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303137/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[312,344,670,693]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[113,144,1333,1352]" captionTargetBox="[163,1044,222,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[150,1053,214,1318]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Third instar larva of Berosus (Berosus) japonicus Sharp, 1873, dorsal; A – head capsule; B – anterior margin of head capsule; C – detail of setae of gFR2; D – spiracular atrium; E – spiracle in spiracular atrium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">5B</figureCitation>
) but present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Laccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and left epistomal lobe bears only stout setae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[210,297,734,757]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[210,297,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[314,409,734,757]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[113,144,912,931]" captionTargetBox="[131,1083,223,861]" captionTargetId="figure-267@9.[113,1088,220,876]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 3. First instar larva of Berosus (Berosus) japonicus Sharp, 1873, anterior margin of head capsule, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) (both drawn from dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303137" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303137/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[424,458,734,757]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[113,144,1333,1352]" captionTargetBox="[163,1044,222,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[150,1053,214,1318]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Third instar larva of Berosus (Berosus) japonicus Sharp, 1873, dorsal; A – head capsule; B – anterior margin of head capsule; C – detail of setae of gFR2; D – spiracular atrium; E – spiracle in spiracular atrium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">5B</figureCitation>
), but bears stout setae and seta-like cuticular projections in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[192,302,798,821]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,302,798,821]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Laccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Y. Minoshima, personal observation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Within Japanese genera, the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Berthold, 1827" authorityName="Berthold" authorityYear="1827" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Hydrochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Hydrochara</emphasis>
Berthold, 1827
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[113,197,926,949]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,197,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of lateral projections on the abdomen (but the projections are not tracheal gills) (
<bibRefCitation author="MINOSHIMA Y. &amp; HAYASHI M." box="[271,580,990,1013]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref17041" refString="MINOSHIMA Y. &amp; HAYASHI M. 2011 a: Larval morphology of the Japanese species of the tribes Acidocerini, Hydrobiusini and Hydrophilini (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 51 (supplementum): 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2011">MINOSHIMA &amp; HAYASHI 2011a</bibRefCitation>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
MINOSHIMA et al. 2012), the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[474,584,1022,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[474,584,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Laccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the head morphology (see above). Larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[141,226,1086,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[141,226,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguishable from those by the above mentioned characters, presence of tracheal gills and absence of spiracular atrium. Additional characters also separate
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[113,201,1214,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,201,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berthold" authorityYear="1827" box="[276,409,1214,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Hydrochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,409,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Hydrochara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (1) mandibles Fig. 1. Habitus of the third instar larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1019,1089,1220,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1089,1220,1239]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strongly asymmetrical; (2) labium more 
<taxonomicName authority="Sharp, 1873" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1873" box="[626,907,1246,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus" subGenus="Berosus">
(
<emphasis box="[633,701,1246,1265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Berosus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[713,796,1246,1265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">japonicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SHARP D." box="[801,907,1246,1265]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="45 - 67" refId="ref17655" refString="SHARP D. 1873: The water beetles of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1873: 45 - 67." type="journal article" year="1873">Sharp, 1873</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,1089,350,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
or less reduced; (3) clypeolabrum strongly asymmetrical, left lobe strongly projecting anteriorly, right lobe absent; (4) legs without swimming hairs; (5) prostyli absent. See also a key to the genera of Japanese aquatic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydrophilidae</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="MINOSHIMA Y. &amp; HAYASHI M." box="[256,585,1374,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref17041" refString="MINOSHIMA Y. &amp; HAYASHI M. 2011 a: Larval morphology of the Japanese species of the tribes Acidocerini, Hydrobiusini and Hydrophilini (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 51 (supplementum): 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2011">MINOSHIMA &amp; HAYASHI (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
